            <section>
                <h2>How to say what you mean</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Be direct</li>
                    <li>Use the active voice</li>
                    <li>Keep it short and simple</li>
                    <li>One sentence, one idea</li>
                    <li>Proof it</li>
                </ul>
            </section>
            <section>
                <h2>Be direct</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Address your readers as ‘you’</li>
                    <li>Refer to yourself as ‘we’ or ‘I’</li>
                    <li class="fragment" data-fragment-index="1">Your writing and its relevance will be easier to understand</li>
                    <li class="fragment" data-fragment-index="1">‘You’ and ‘we’ make writing more confident, transparent and personal</li>
                    <li class="fragment" data-fragment-index="2">Write about what concerns your reader</li>
                </ul>
            </section>
            <section>
                <section>
                    <h2>Use the active voice</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li>The single biggest thing to make your writing more engaging</li>
                        <li class="separate fragment">
                            Passive voice:
                            <p class="indent correct">‘All of the mistakes were made by him’</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="fragment">
                            Active voice:
                            <p class="indent incorrect">‘He made all of the mistakes’</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2>Use the active voice</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li>The passive voice puts the action first</li>
                        <li>The active voice puts the ‘doer’ first</li>
                        <li class="fragment" data-fragment-index="1">Clearer</li>
                        <li class="fragment" data-fragment-index="1">Less clumsy/academic</li>
                        <li class="fragment" data-fragment-index="1">More concise</li>
                        <li class="fragment" data-fragment-index="1">More interesting</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2>Use the active voice</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Look out for ‘was’ and ‘by’
                            <ul>
                                <li>‘The report was written by me’</li>
                                <li>‘Her birthday was celebrated’</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li class="fragment">
                            Or when there is no ‘doer’
                            <ul>
                                <li>‘The files will be sent as soon as possible’</li>
                                <li>‘All our records have been lost’</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </section>
            </section>
            <section>
                <section>
                    <h2>Keep it short and simple</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Use everyday language</li>
                        <li>
                            Edit what you’ve written
                            <ul>
                                <li>Are you using the best word for the job?</li>
                                <li>What do you mean?</li>
                                <li>Is there a simpler way to say it?</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li class="fragment">When you’re finished, try cutting the content by a third</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2>Keep it short and simple</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Verbs make language dynamic</li>
                        <li class="fragment" data-fragment-index="1">
                            Watch out for ‘nominalisation’
                            <ul>
                                <li>Creating a noun from a verb</li>
                                <li class="fragment" data-fragment-index="2">Use <span class="correct">consider</span> not <span class="incorrect">give consideration to</span></li>
                                <li class="fragment" data-fragment-index="2">Use <span class="correct">decide</span>, not <span class="incorrect">reach a decision</span></li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li class="fragment">
                            Be concrete rather than abstract
                            <ul class="fragment">
                                <li><span class="incorrect">Employment opportunities</span> = <span class="correct">jobs</span></li>
                                <li><span class="incorrect">Achieve the objective</span> = <span class="correct">release on the 30th</span></li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </section>
            </section>
            <section>
                <h2>One sentence, one idea</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Keep your sentences short</li>
                    <li>One idea per sentence</li>
                    <li>Long sentences are hard to follow and understand</li>
                    <li>Varying the rhythm of your sentences keep them engaging</li>
                    <li>Try to stick to one main point per paragraph</li>
                </ul>
            </section>
            <section>
                <h2>Proof it</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Proofreading is not an optional extra</li>
                    <li>Come back to proof when you’re fresh</li>
                    <li>Perhaps ask someone else</li>
                    <li>In some cases, printing it might be useful</li>
                </ul>
            </section>
            <section>
                <h2>Top ten tips</h2>
                <ol class="smaller">
                    <li>Know your reader</li>
                    <li>Know what you want to say</li>
                    <li>Be direct</li>
                    <li>Use the active voice</li>
                    <li>Keep it short and simple</li>
                    <li>One sentence, one idea</li>
                    <li>Keep paragraphs short</li>
                    <li>Use subheadings that summarise your content</li>
                    <li>Edit, then edit again</li>
                    <li>Proofread when you’re fresh</li>
                </ol>
            </section>
            <section>
                <blockquote>I try to leave out the parts that people skip</blockquote>
